Hi Wonder,

Fonts are made with software. There are several programs available to do it.
I use one called Font Creator Program or FCP. I say I&#39;ve used it. It&#39;s more
like I&#39;ve tried it. It works but it seems a bit cumbersome. It has the
advantage of costing a few tens of dollars. There may be some other programs
out there that are expensive, but the others I know about are several
hundreds of dollars. The address of FCP is www.high-logic.com
&lt;http://www.high-logic.com/&gt; .

I use the Read alphabet to keep a journal. Unfortunately, I&#39;m unaware of a
dictionary for the Read Alphabet. However, it is completely phonetic so in
principle you can pick any dictionary that spells words phonetically and use
it to spell using the Read alphabet. However, this is a bit cumbersome.
Also, there is disagreement among dictionaries about how words are
pronounced. Some who use the Read alphabet are not too concerned about this
and maintain these relative differences in spelling are not important. I
tend to agree, but even if true, I sometimes find it difficult to spell the
words without fairly major errors. So I think a dictionary would be nice for
beginners. It would be a good project to draft one.

I&#39;m not sure I understood your questions regarding punctuation. I can&#39;t
quite imagine connecting a period to the letters in a pleasing way.

Good Wishes,



